.TH "diag_ftp_2c4" 9 "diag_ftp_2c4" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
diag_ftp_2c4 \- DIAGNOSE X'2C4' service call
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" diag_ftp_2c4
.BI "(struct diag_ftp_ldfpl *fpl "  ","
.BI "enum hmcdrv_ftp_cmdid cmd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fpl" 12
pointer to prepared LDFPL
.IP "cmd" 12
FTP command to be executed
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Performs a DIAGNOSE X'2C4' call with (input/output) FTP parameter list
\fIfpl\fP and FTP function code \fIcmd\fP. In case of an error the function does
nothing and returns an (negative) error code.
.SH "NOTES"
1. This function only initiates a transfer, so the caller must wait
for completion (asynchronous execution).
2. The FTP parameter list \fIfpl\fP must be aligned to a double-word boundary.
3. fpl->bufaddr must be a real address, 4k aligned
